{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"DRUPAL-CONTRIB-2019-068","published":"2019-09-25T14:43:49Z","modified":"2025-12-10T23:32:38.259465Z","details":"This module enables you to control access to content based on taxonomy terms. The module doesn't sufficiently check if a given entity should be access controlled, defaulting to allowing access even to unpublished nodes.\n\nThe vulnerability is mitigated by the fact that the submodule Permissions by Entity must also be enabled.","affected":[{"package":{"name":"drupal/permissions_by_term","ecosystem":"Packagist:https://packages.drupal.org/8","purl":"pkg:composer/drupal/permissions_by_term"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"2.11.0"}],"database_specific":{"constraint":"<2.11.0"}}],"database_specific":{"affected_versions":"<2.11.0","source":"https://github.com/DrupalSecurityTeam/drupal-advisory-database/blob/main/advisories/permissions_by_term/DRUPAL-CONTRIB-2019-068.json"}}],"references":[{"type":"WEB","url":"https://www.drupal.org/sa-contrib-2019-068"}],"credits":[{"name":"Jimmy Henderickx","contact":["https://www.drupal.org/user/462700"]}]}